IMAPAccount personal
Host imap.gmail.com
User me@kfring.com
PassCmd "gpg2 -q --for-your-eyes-only --batch --yes --no-tty -d ~/.mbsyncpass.personal.gpg"
Port 993
SSLType IMAPS
AuthMechs Login
CertificateFile /etc/ssl/certs/ca-certificates.crt 

IMAPStore personal-remote
Account personal

MaildirStore personal-local
Path ~/.mail/kfring/
Inbox ~/.mail/kfring/inbox

Channel personal-main
Master :personal-remote:
Slave :personal-local:
# NOTE: empty lines matter to mbsync when it reads in the config.
Patterns "INBOX" "Arch*"
# Create missing mailboxes on both locally and on the server.
Create Both
Expunge Both
SyncState *
# ref: https://chrisstreeter.com/archive/2009/04/gmail-imap-backup-with-mbsync-on-ubuntu.html
# Maybe we'll do this later.
# ref: https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/Isync#Step_#2:_Setup_mbsync
# Exclude everything under the internal [Gmail] folder, except the interesting folders
# Patterns * !"[Gmail]/All Mail" !"[Gmail]/Important" !"[Gmail]/Starred" !"[Gmail]/Trash"
# Patterns * !"[Gmail]/All Mail" !"[Gmail]/Important" !"[Gmail]/Starred" !"[Gmail]/Trash" !"[Gmail]/Spam" !"[Gmail]/Sent Mail"
# Or include everything
# Patterns *

Channel personal-trash
Master :personal-remote:"[Gmail]/Trash"
Slave :personal-local:trash
Create Both
Expunge Both
SyncState *

Channel personal-sent
Master :personal-remote:"[Gmail]/Sent Mail"
Slave :personal-local:sent
Create Both
Expunge Both
SyncState *

Channel personal-drafts
Master :personal-remote:"[Gmail]/Drafts"
Slave :personal-local:drafts
Create Both
Expunge Both
SyncState *

Channel personal-all
Master :personal-remote:"[Gmail]/All Mail"
Slave :personal-local:"[Gmail].All Mail"
Create Both
Expunge Both
SyncState *

Channel personal-starred
Master :personal-remote:"[Gmail]/Starred"
Slave :personal-local:"[Gmail].Starred"
Create Both
Expunge Both
SyncState *

Group personal
Channel personal-starred
Channel personal-all
Channel personal-drafts
Channel personal-sent
Channel personal-trash
Channel personal-main
